<body>

  <!-- ===== COVER / TITLE ===== -->
  <div class="doc-header">
    <h1>Assured Shorthold Tenancy Agreement</h1>
    <div class="doc-subtitle">Housing Act 1988 (as amended)</div>
    <div class="doc-subtitle">England</div>
    <div class="doc-date">Dated: <strong>{{formatUKDate agreement_date}}</strong></div>
  </div>

  <!-- ===== 1. PARTIES ===== -->
  <h2>1. Parties</h2>
  <div class="parties-section">
    <div class="party-block">
      <div class="party-role">Landlord</div>
      <div class="party-details-text">
        <strong>{{landlord_full_name}}</strong><br>
        <span class="address-text">{{landlord_address}}</span><br>
        <span class="email-text">{{landlord_email}}</span> | {{landlord_phone}}
      </div>
    </div>

    {{#if agent_name}}
    <div class="party-block">
      <div class="party-role">Landlord's Agent</div>
      <div class="party-details-text">
        <strong>{{agent_name}}</strong><br>
        <span class="address-text">{{agent_address}}</span><br>
        <span class="email-text">{{agent_email}}</span> | {{agent_phone}}
      </div>
    </div>
    {{/if}}

    <div class="party-block">
      <div class="party-role">Tenant{{#if multiple_tenants}}s{{/if}}</div>
      <div class="party-details-text">
        {{#each tenants}}
        <strong>{{this.full_name}}</strong>{{#if this.dob}} (DOB: {{formatUKDate this.dob}}){{/if}}<br>
        <span class="email-text">{{this.email}}</span>{{#if this.phone}} | {{this.phone}}{{/if}}{{#unless @last}}<br><br>{{/unless}}
        {{/each}}
      </div>
    </div>

    {{#if guarantor_name}}
    <div class="party-block">
      <div class="party-role">Guarantor</div>
      <div class="party-details-text">
        <strong>{{guarantor_name}}</strong><br>
        <span class="address-text">{{guarantor_address}}</span><br>
        <span class="email-text">{{guarantor_email}}</span> | {{guarantor_phone}}
      </div>
    </div>
    {{/if}}
  </div>

  <!-- ===== 2. DEFINITIONS ===== -->
  <h2>2. Definitions and Interpretation</h2>
  <p>In this Agreement, unless the context requires otherwise:</p>
  <ul class="definitions-list">
    <li><span class="defined-term">"Agreement"</span> means this tenancy agreement and the Schedules attached.</li>
    <li><span class="defined-term">"Landlord"</span> means {{landlord_full_name}} and successors in title.</li>
    {{#if agent_name}}<li><span class="defined-term">"Agent"</span> means {{agent_name}}, the Landlord's authorised agent.</li>{{/if}}
    <li><span class="defined-term">"Tenant"</span> means {{#each tenants}}{{this.full_name}}{{#unless @last}}, {{/unless}}{{/each}}{{#if multiple_tenants}} (jointly and severally){{/if}}.</li>
    {{#if guarantor_name}}<li><span class="defined-term">"Guarantor"</span> means {{guarantor_name}}.</li>{{/if}}
    <li><span class="defined-term">"Property"</span> means {{property_address}} as described in Schedule 1.</li>
    <li><span class="defined-term">"Term"</span> means the {{#if is_fixed_term}}fixed term from {{formatUKDate tenancy_start_date}} to {{formatUKDate tenancy_end_date}}{{else}}periodic tenancy from {{formatUKDate tenancy_start_date}}{{/if}} and any continuation.</li>
    <li><span class="defined-term">"Rent"</span> means £{{rent_amount}} per {{rent_period}} as set out in Schedule 2.</li>
    <li><span class="defined-term">"Deposit"</span> means £{{deposit_amount}} held in {{deposit_scheme_name}} as set out in Schedule 2.</li>
    <li><span class="defined-term">"Scheme"</span> means the government-authorised deposit protection scheme.</li>
    <li><span class="defined-term">"Contents"</span> means furniture and items listed in any inventory.</li>
    <li><span class="defined-term">"Written Notice"</span> means notice in writing by hand, post, or email.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Words importing the singular include the plural. Where there is more than one Tenant, their obligations are joint and several.</p>

  <!-- ===== 3. THE PROPERTY ===== -->
  <h2>3. The Property</h2>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">3.1</span> The Landlord lets to the Tenant the Property described in Schedule 1 for the Term, together with any Contents listed in the inventory.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">3.2</span> The Property is let for use as a private residential dwelling only.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">3.3</span> The Landlord warrants that all necessary compliance certificates are valid and have been or will be provided to the Tenant.</p>

  <!-- ===== 4. THE TERM ===== -->
  <h2>4. The Term</h2>
  {{#if is_fixed_term}}
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">4.1</span> The tenancy begins on <strong>{{formatUKDate tenancy_start_date}}</strong> and ends on <strong>{{formatUKDate tenancy_end_date}}</strong> (the "Fixed Term").</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">4.2</span> Upon expiry of the Fixed Term, unless either party serves notice, the tenancy continues as a statutory periodic tenancy on the same terms.</p>
  {{else}}
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">4.1</span> The tenancy begins on <strong>{{formatUKDate tenancy_start_date}}</strong> as a periodic (monthly) tenancy.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">4.2</span> The tenancy continues until terminated by either party giving proper notice.</p>
  {{/if}}
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">4.3</span> The Landlord may seek possession using Section 21 (no-fault, minimum 2 months' notice) or Section 8 (fault-based) of the Housing Act 1988.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">4.4</span> The Tenant may end the tenancy by giving at least one month's written notice expiring on a rent due date.</p>

  <!-- ===== 5. RENT ===== -->
  <h2>5. Rent</h2>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">5.1</span> The Tenant shall pay the Rent of <strong>£{{rent_amount}}</strong> per {{rent_period}} in advance on the <strong>{{rent_due_day}}</strong> of each {{rent_period}}.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">5.2</span> Payment shall be made by {{payment_method}} to the account specified in Schedule 2.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">5.3</span> The first payment is due on or before {{formatUKDate tenancy_start_date}}.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">5.4</span> If rent remains unpaid for 14 days after the due date, interest may accrue at 3% above the Bank of England base rate per annum.</p>

  <!-- ===== 6. DEPOSIT ===== -->
  <h2>6. Deposit</h2>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">6.1</span> The Tenant has paid a Deposit of <strong>£{{deposit_amount}}</strong>.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">6.2</span> The Landlord will protect the Deposit in {{deposit_scheme_name}} within 30 days and provide the prescribed information.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">6.3</span> The Deposit may be applied against unpaid rent, damage beyond fair wear and tear, cleaning costs, missing inventory items, or other sums due under this Agreement.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">6.4</span> Any dispute over deductions may be referred to the Scheme's free alternative dispute resolution service.</p>

  <!-- ===== 7. TENANT OBLIGATIONS ===== -->
  <h2>7. Tenant Obligations</h2>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">7.1</span> <strong>Rent:</strong> Pay the Rent on time and in full.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">7.2</span> <strong>Utilities:</strong> Pay all charges for gas, electricity, water, council tax, telephone, and internet as set out in Schedule 3.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">7.3</span> <strong>Care of Property:</strong> Keep the Property clean and in good condition, not cause damage, and promptly report any disrepair to the Landlord.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">7.4</span> <strong>Access:</strong> Allow the Landlord (with reasonable notice of at least 24 hours, except in emergency) to enter the Property for inspection, repairs, or to show prospective tenants or buyers.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">7.5</span> <strong>Use:</strong> Use the Property only as a private residence and comply with the House Rules in Schedule 5.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">7.6</span> <strong>Nuisance:</strong> Not cause nuisance, annoyance, or disturbance to neighbours.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">7.7</span> <strong>Subletting:</strong> Not sublet, assign, or part with possession without the Landlord's prior written consent.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">7.8</span> <strong>Alterations:</strong> Not make alterations to the Property without the Landlord's prior written consent.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">7.9</span> <strong>Insurance:</strong> Not do anything that would invalidate the Landlord's insurance.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">7.10</span> <strong>End of Tenancy:</strong> Return the Property at the end of the tenancy in the same condition as at the start (fair wear and tear excepted), return all keys, and provide a forwarding address.</p>

  <!-- ===== 8. LANDLORD OBLIGATIONS ===== -->
  <h2>8. Landlord Obligations</h2>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">8.1</span> <strong>Quiet Enjoyment:</strong> Allow the Tenant to occupy the Property without interference, except as permitted by this Agreement.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">8.2</span> <strong>Repairs:</strong> Keep the structure, exterior, and installations for water, gas, electricity, heating, and sanitation in repair and proper working order.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">8.3</span> <strong>Safety:</strong> Ensure the Property has valid Gas Safety Certificate, Electrical Installation Condition Report, smoke and carbon monoxide alarms, and an Energy Performance Certificate rating of E or above.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">8.4</span> <strong>Deposit:</strong> Protect the Deposit in a government-authorised scheme and provide prescribed information within 30 days.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">8.5</span> <strong>Documents:</strong> Provide the Tenant with the current How to Rent guide, EPC, Gas Safety Certificate, and EICR before the tenancy starts or as soon as reasonably practicable.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">8.6</span> <strong>Insurance:</strong> Maintain buildings insurance for the Property.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">8.7</span> <strong>Right to Rent:</strong> The Landlord confirms that the required Right to Rent checks have been carried out in accordance with the Immigration Act 2014 before the Tenant occupies the Property. Nothing in this Agreement makes the Tenant responsible for the Landlord's compliance with Right to Rent requirements.</p>

  {{#if guarantor_name}}
  <!-- ===== 9. GUARANTOR ===== -->
  <h2>9. Guarantor</h2>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">9.1</span> The Guarantor guarantees the Tenant's obligations under this Agreement and agrees to be jointly and severally liable with the Tenant.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">9.2</span> If the Tenant fails to pay rent or breaches any obligation, the Guarantor will pay or remedy the breach on demand.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">9.3</span> This guarantee continues throughout the tenancy including any periodic continuation.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">9.4</span> The Guarantor's liability is capped at twelve months' rent plus reasonable enforcement costs.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">9.5</span> The Guarantor confirms they have been advised to seek independent legal advice before signing.</p>
  {{/if}}

  <!-- ===== 10. GENERAL ===== -->
  <h2>{{#if guarantor_name}}10{{else}}9{{/if}}. General Provisions</h2>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">{{#if guarantor_name}}10{{else}}9{{/if}}.1</span> This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement between the parties.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">{{#if guarantor_name}}10{{else}}9{{/if}}.2</span> No variation is effective unless in writing and signed by all parties.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">{{#if guarantor_name}}10{{else}}9{{/if}}.3</span> This Agreement is governed by the laws of England and Wales.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">{{#if guarantor_name}}10{{else}}9{{/if}}.4</span> Notices may be served by hand, first-class post, or email to the addresses given in this Agreement.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">{{#if guarantor_name}}10{{else}}9{{/if}}.5</span> If any provision is unenforceable, the remaining provisions continue in effect.</p>

  <!-- ===== SIGNATURES ===== -->
  <div class="signature-section">
    <h2>Signatures</h2>
    <p>By signing below, the parties confirm they have read, understood, and agree to be bound by all terms of this Agreement and the attached Schedules.</p>

    <div class="signature-block">
      <div class="signature-role">Landlord</div>
      <div class="signature-name">Name: {{landlord_full_name}}</div>
      <div class="signature-line"></div>
      <div class="signature-label">Signature</div>
      <div style="margin-top: 10pt;">Date: <span class="signature-date-line"></span></div>
    </div>

    {{#if agent_name}}
    <div class="signature-block">
      <div class="signature-role">Agent (signing on behalf of Landlord)</div>
      <div class="signature-name">Name: {{agent_name}}</div>
      <div class="signature-line"></div>
      <div class="signature-label">Signature</div>
      <div style="margin-top: 10pt;">Date: <span class="signature-date-line"></span></div>
    </div>
    {{/if}}

    {{#each tenants}}
    <div class="signature-block">
      <div class="signature-role">Tenant {{add @index 1}}</div>
      <div class="signature-name">Name: {{this.full_name}}</div>
      <div class="signature-line"></div>
      <div class="signature-label">Signature</div>
      <div style="margin-top: 10pt;">Date: <span class="signature-date-line"></span></div>
    </div>
    {{/each}}

    {{#if guarantor_name}}
    <div class="signature-block">
      <div class="signature-role">Guarantor</div>
      <div class="signature-name">Name: {{guarantor_name}}</div>
      <div class="signature-line"></div>
      <div class="signature-label">Signature</div>
      <div style="margin-top: 10pt;">Date: <span class="signature-date-line"></span></div>
    </div>
    {{/if}}
  </div>

  <!-- ===== SCHEDULE 1: PROPERTY ===== -->
  <section class="schedule">
    <div class="schedule-header">
      <h2>Schedule 1</h2>
      <div class="schedule-title">Property Details</div>
    </div>

    <table class="data-table">
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Property Address</td>
        <td class="value address-text">{{property_address}}</td>
      </tr>
      {{#if property_type}}
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Property Type</td>
        <td class="value">{{property_type}}</td>
      </tr>
      {{/if}}
      {{#if number_of_bedrooms}}
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Bedrooms</td>
        <td class="value">{{number_of_bedrooms}}</td>
      </tr>
      {{/if}}
      {{#if furnished_status}}
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Furnished Status</td>
        <td class="value">{{#eq furnished_status "furnished"}}Furnished{{/eq}}{{#eq furnished_status "unfurnished"}}Unfurnished{{/eq}}{{#eq furnished_status "part-furnished"}}Part-Furnished{{/eq}}{{#unless (eq furnished_status "furnished")}}{{#unless (eq furnished_status "unfurnished")}}{{#unless (eq furnished_status "part-furnished")}}{{furnished_status}}{{/unless}}{{/unless}}{{/unless}}</td>
      </tr>
      {{/if}}
      {{#if council_tax_band}}
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Council Tax Band</td>
        <td class="value">{{council_tax_band}}</td>
      </tr>
      {{/if}}
      {{#if epc_rating}}
      <tr>
        <td class="label">EPC Rating</td>
        <td class="value">{{epc_rating}}</td>
      </tr>
      {{/if}}
      {{#if parking_available}}
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Parking</td>
        <td class="value">{{#if parking_details}}{{parking_details}}{{else}}Included{{/if}}</td>
      </tr>
      {{/if}}
    </table>

    <h3>Compliance Certificates</h3>
    <table class="data-table">
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Gas Safety Certificate</td>
        <td class="value">{{#if gas_safety_certificate}}Valid{{#if gas_safety_certificate_expiry}} (expires {{formatUKDate gas_safety_certificate_expiry}}){{/if}}{{else}}To be provided{{/if}}</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="label">EICR</td>
        <td class="value">{{#if electrical_safety_certificate}}Valid{{#if eicr_next_inspection_date}} (next inspection {{formatUKDate eicr_next_inspection_date}}){{/if}}{{else}}To be provided{{/if}}</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="label">EPC</td>
        <td class="value">{{#if epc_rating}}Rating {{epc_rating}}{{#if epc_expiry}} (valid until {{formatUKDate epc_expiry}}){{/if}}{{else}}To be provided{{/if}}</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Smoke Alarms</td>
        <td class="value">{{#if smoke_alarms_fitted}}Fitted{{else}}Fitted (legally required){{/if}}</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="label">CO Alarms</td>
        <td class="value">{{#if carbon_monoxide_alarms}}Fitted{{else}}Fitted where required{{/if}}</td>
      </tr>
    </table>

    <h3>Mandatory Documents</h3>
    <p>The Landlord confirms the following have been or will be provided to the Tenant:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Current How to Rent guide (latest government version)</li>
      <li>Energy Performance Certificate</li>
      <li>Gas Safety Certificate (annually)</li>
      <li>Electrical Installation Condition Report</li>
      <li>Deposit protection prescribed information (within 30 days)</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== SCHEDULE 2: RENT & DEPOSIT ===== -->
  <section class="schedule">
    <div class="schedule-header">
      <h2>Schedule 2</h2>
      <div class="schedule-title">Rent and Deposit</div>
    </div>

    <h3>Part A: Rent</h3>
    <table class="data-table">
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Rent Amount</td>
        <td class="value">£{{rent_amount}} per {{rent_period}}</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Payment Due</td>
        <td class="value">{{rent_due_day}} of each {{rent_period}}</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Payment Method</td>
        <td class="value">{{payment_method}}</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="label">First Payment</td>
        <td class="value">{{#if first_payment_date}}{{formatUKDate first_payment_date}}{{else}}{{formatUKDate tenancy_start_date}}{{/if}}</td>
      </tr>
    </table>

    <h4>Bank Details</h4>
    <table class="data-table">
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Account Name</td>
        <td class="value">{{#if bank_account_name}}{{bank_account_name}}{{else}}{{landlord_full_name}}{{/if}}</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Sort Code</td>
        <td class="value">{{bank_sort_code}}</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Account Number</td>
        <td class="value">{{bank_account_number}}</td>
      </tr>
    </table>

    <h3>Part B: Deposit</h3>
    <table class="data-table">
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Deposit Amount</td>
        <td class="value">£{{deposit_amount}}</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Protection Scheme</td>
        <td class="value">{{deposit_scheme_name}}</td>
      </tr>
    </table>

    <div class="legal-notice">
      <div class="legal-notice-title">Deposit Protection</div>
      <p>The Deposit will be protected within 30 days and prescribed information provided. At tenancy end, the Deposit (less any lawful deductions) will be returned via the Scheme's procedures. Disputes may be referred to the Scheme's free ADR service.</p>
    </div>

    <h4>Permitted Deductions</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Unpaid rent or other sums due</li>
      <li>Damage beyond fair wear and tear</li>
      <li>Missing inventory items</li>
      <li>Cleaning costs if not left in comparable condition</li>
      <li>Unreturned keys or access devices</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== SCHEDULE 3: UTILITIES ===== -->
  <section class="schedule">
    <div class="schedule-header">
      <h2>Schedule 3</h2>
      <div class="schedule-title">Utilities and Services</div>
    </div>

    <table class="data-table">
      <tr>
        <th style="width: 40%;">Utility</th>
        <th style="width: 30%;">Responsibility</th>
        <th style="width: 30%;">Notes</th>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Council Tax</td>
        <td>{{#if council_tax_responsibility}}{{council_tax_responsibility}}{{else}}Tenant{{/if}}</td>
        <td>{{#if council_tax_band}}Band {{council_tax_band}}{{/if}}</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Gas</td>
        <td>{{#if utilities_responsibility}}{{utilities_responsibility}}{{else}}Tenant{{/if}}</td>
        <td>Register with supplier</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Electricity</td>
        <td>{{#if utilities_responsibility}}{{utilities_responsibility}}{{else}}Tenant{{/if}}</td>
        <td>Register with supplier</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Water</td>
        <td>{{#if utilities_responsibility}}{{utilities_responsibility}}{{else}}Tenant{{/if}}</td>
        <td></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Internet</td>
        <td>{{#if internet_responsibility}}{{internet_responsibility}}{{else}}Tenant{{/if}}</td>
        <td></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>TV Licence</td>
        <td>Tenant</td>
        <td>If required</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Buildings Insurance</td>
        <td>Landlord</td>
        <td>Tenant arranges contents</td>
      </tr>
    </table>

    <p>The Tenant must notify utility suppliers of occupation within 7 days and provide meter readings at start and end of tenancy.</p>

    {{#if meter_reading_gas}}{{#if meter_reading_electric}}
    <h3>Meter Readings at Start</h3>
    <table class="data-table">
      {{#if meter_reading_gas}}<tr><td class="label">Gas</td><td class="value">{{meter_reading_gas}}</td></tr>{{/if}}
      {{#if meter_reading_electric}}<tr><td class="label">Electricity</td><td class="value">{{meter_reading_electric}}</td></tr>{{/if}}
      {{#if meter_reading_water}}<tr><td class="label">Water</td><td class="value">{{meter_reading_water}}</td></tr>{{/if}}
    </table>
    {{/if}}{{/if}}
  </section>

  <!-- ===== SCHEDULE 4: INVENTORY ===== -->
  <section class="schedule">
    <div class="schedule-header">
      <h2>Schedule 4</h2>
      <div class="schedule-title">Inventory and Condition</div>
    </div>

    {{#if inventory_attached}}
    <p>A detailed inventory and schedule of condition is attached or provided separately and forms part of this Agreement.</p>
    {{else}}
    <p>{{#if inventory_provided}}An inventory will be provided at or before the start of the tenancy.{{else}}The Tenant should prepare a photographic record of the Property's condition at the start of the tenancy.{{/if}}</p>
    {{/if}}

    <h3>Keys and Access Devices</h3>
    <table class="data-table">
      {{#if number_of_front_door_keys}}<tr><td class="label">Front Door Keys</td><td class="value">{{number_of_front_door_keys}}</td></tr>{{/if}}
      {{#if number_of_back_door_keys}}<tr><td class="label">Back Door Keys</td><td class="value">{{number_of_back_door_keys}}</td></tr>{{/if}}
      {{#if access_cards_fobs}}<tr><td class="label">Access Cards/Fobs</td><td class="value">{{access_cards_fobs}}</td></tr>{{/if}}
      {{#if number_of_mailbox_keys}}<tr><td class="label">Mailbox Keys</td><td class="value">{{number_of_mailbox_keys}}</td></tr>{{/if}}
    </table>
    <p>All keys must be returned at tenancy end. Lost key replacement will be charged to the Tenant.</p>

    <h3>Condition at End of Tenancy</h3>
    <p>The Tenant must return the Property in the same condition as at the start (fair wear and tear excepted). A check-out inspection will be conducted, preferably with the Tenant present.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== SCHEDULE 5: HOUSE RULES ===== -->
  <section class="schedule">
    <div class="schedule-header">
      <h2>Schedule 5</h2>
      <div class="schedule-title">House Rules</div>
    </div>

    <h3>Permitted Use</h3>
    <p>The Property is let for use as a private residential dwelling only. The Tenant must not use the Property for trade or business, or do anything causing nuisance to neighbours.</p>

    <h3>Pets</h3>
    <table class="data-table">
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Pets Permitted</td>
        <td class="value">{{#if pets_allowed}}Yes{{#if approved_pets}} ({{approved_pets}}){{/if}}{{else}}No (consent required){{/if}}</td>
      </tr>
    </table>
    {{#if pets_allowed}}
    <p>Approved pets must be kept under control, not cause nuisance, and be up to date with vaccinations. The Tenant is liable for any pet damage.</p>
    {{else}}
    <p>The Tenant may request consent for pets in writing. The Landlord will not unreasonably refuse well-behaved pets.</p>
    {{/if}}

    <h3>Smoking</h3>
    <table class="data-table">
      <tr>
        <td class="label">Smoking Permitted</td>
        <td class="value">{{#if smoking_allowed}}Outdoors only{{else}}No{{/if}}</td>
      </tr>
    </table>

    <h3>Subletting</h3>
    <p>The Tenant must not sublet, take in lodgers, or list the Property on short-term letting platforms without prior written consent. Unauthorised subletting is a serious breach.</p>

    <h3>Quiet Enjoyment</h3>
    <p>The Tenant must behave considerately, keep noise reasonable (especially 11pm-7am), and ensure visitors respect these rules.</p>

    {{#if has_garden}}
    <h3>Garden</h3>
    <p>The Tenant is responsible for keeping the garden in reasonable condition: mowing lawns, trimming hedges, and keeping paths clear.</p>
    {{/if}}

    <h3>Alterations</h3>
    <p>No alterations without prior written consent. Minor picture hooks may be permitted. Any alterations become the Landlord's property.</p>
  </section>

